node.text:
This Halloween we decided to throw a Hocus Pocus themed family party at home, and watch the movie now available on Digital in 4K Ultra HD. October is going to be a crazy month for us! We’ll be packing up and moving to Nashville but I’m not sure if we’ll make it in time for Halloween. So instead, we decided to celebrate Halloween at home, before the move, and the kids LOVED IT! #ad 
.
.
We made Spellbook Brownies, Mummy Dogs, Dead Mans Toes, Life Potion, and Amuck-Amuck-AMUNCH (watch the video for how-to’s). Combine that with a fog machine, trick-or-treating around the house, and a Hocus Pocus movie night and you’ve got yourself a Halloween Party! We watch the beloved classic Hocus Pocus every year but this year it was crystal clear on the big screen in 4K Ultra HD and it always serves as the BEST kickoff to our holiday season. 
.
.
What are your plans for Halloween?
@disney #hocuspocus

node.text: We had ZERO plans but we did it! We made the bunk room of OUR dreams. ✨ Oh, and the kids like it too. 😂👌🏻 What are some questions you have about the space? If it’s about the DIY I’ll grab Brad (maybe I can even get him to do a live q&a) if it’s about the decor I’M ALL EARS. 👂🏻👂🏻Thanks for being here with us for another fun project, friends! 👐🏻 Now onto the next!

www.homedepot.com/decor #homedepotpartner

node.text: Time for a little Master Bedroom Room Refresh with HomeDepot.com/decor! Fresh linens, cute throw blankets, new greenery, nightstands, and rug…loving the calm, airy vibe in here. 🌿 Oh, and can we talk about those new yummy leather benches at the end of the bed?? I’ve got all of the products linked on the blog (link in profile). @homedepot #homedepotpartner

I’m SURE grateful for designers out there with an amazing eye! If I could do college over again I would gone into design. 👩🏻‍🎨(Sidenote: did you know I got my degree in Elementary Education? 👩🏻‍🏫)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by holly+brad |ourfauxfarmhouse on August 25, 2021 tagging @reflectionsofchrist. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text:
I just need this pic to have a place right here. 
.
.
I should start by saying that this is not in ANY way meant to be a political post, so please don’t take it as that. 
.
.
The world is just so upside down right now. I don’t know about you, but over the past couple of years I’ve grown increasingly confused as to whom I can trust. The media is full of sensational headlines and scare tactics, our government officials contradict themselves and leave me feeling more confused than ever. I keep feeling like no matter what—I don’t know where to turn to or whom to trust for direction and answers? 
.
.
And then I sat in my hallway last week and took this pic. It’s like I had forgotten who’s really in charge here. Some might unfollow for me posting a picture of Christ—and that’s fine. But this is my public declaration that this is MY leader. And I am His follower. I know who wins in the end. So this is me, surrendering my will, buckling up and trying to enjoy the ride. Hopefully this picture brings you peace, if that’s what you’re searching for. 🤍

node.text:
Getting some good use out of Rae’s Retreat (craft room ✂️)…which is good bc since converting this space we have ZERO storage space in this house anymore. 😬🤭 But it’s ALL worth it for this little girl. 
.
.
This week we got to try Cricut’s newest smart cutting machine—The Cricut Maker 3 and my mind is blown! 🤯 It can cut over 300+ materials and doesn’t even require a cutting mat! It engraves, debosses, cuts through thick leather and even some types of wood! 😳 Sky’s the limit when DIYing, crafting, and creating with the Cricut Maker 3! And don’t forget this cute little gift wrapping station that we turned into our Cricut Cart. It stores all of our vinyl + supplies AND holds those pesky tubes of gift wrap. 🙌🏻
.
.
Now for the fun part, will you believe me when I tell you that I got BOTH of these items (the Cricut + Craft Cart) at homedepot.com/decor? Welp, I did. 👏🏻 So many incredible items for your home in that section of their website. Look there and check out their affordable prices before buying on other websites. Their selections and vast offerings will surprise you!! @homedepot #HomeDepotPartner #HomeDepotDecor

node.text:
We love you, Remi girl. 🐶 You were such a good little pup. You blessed our family with so much joy and happiness over the past 18 months. You NEVER made a stranger and ALWAYS made everyone around you smile. (I wanna be more like Remi.) You had the BIGGEST hops for the tiniest little body. You were our best friend. Milo’s BEST best friend, and little sister (they had the same parents/different litters). We will never understand why your life had to be cut short—you’re the first big loss for the kids, and one that will not be easy to get over. 😔 But you’ve already taught them and us so much. We are so grateful for the time we got with you. We like to think you’re in heaven jumping off all of the tiny little curbs with your mad hops. 🐇 We’ll miss you pup. You were the best girl. 🤍 
.
.
I won’t go into a lot of detail—but after a long week of ups and downs Remi passed shortly after having seizures caused by what was suspected to be auto-immune encephalitis. There was nothing we could do to save her. We are devastated but appreciate your kind words so much. We’ll be back on stories tomorrow but I’m not sure I’ll talk about this. We’re just……needing to heal. 🤍🤍🐶🐶

node.text:
The ceiling treatment is DONE!! {swipe for before} It adds so much character to the entire space. 🙌🏻✨ Y’all are troopers for following along on this one. Turns out making the faux beams was the easiest part of the whole thing. 😆🤭 If we didn’t convince you to shiplap the ceiling, did we at least convince you to add faux beams SOMEWHERE in your house? 
.
.
And just wanted to say a BIG huge THANK YOU for following along on our DIY adventures these past 58 months. Holy cow…we’ve been doing this 58 months. 🤭 We are taking the next month off IG to be with our kids for the second half of summer and to finish building out our first brick + mortar @urbansips in Franklin. We’ll see y’all in August, FAUX FAM! We’ll miss you!! #diy #diyprojects
